             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am brother to 
               <persName id="t17810530-34-person361">
                  Griffith
                   Jones
               <interp inst="t17810530-34-person361" type="surname" value="Jones"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17810530-34-person361" type="given" value="Griffith"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17810530-34-person361" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Upon the 30th of April, as I was coming to my brother, at about half after eight o'clock, or thereabouts, I saw a person look in at the shop window; I went to the post of the door, and turned round to look at him: as soon as he observed me look at him, he went up a gateway; I went about five doors farther; I came back, and saw a man run across Monument-yard, with a parcel of clothes under his arm; but I cannot tell who that man was.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I heard a person cry, Stop thief! I ran across into Cannon-street, and this man came and laid hold of me. I never had any clothes. I was making the best of my way over the water.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17810530-34-verdict158" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17810530-34-verdict158" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Tried by the London Jury, before Mr. Justice WILLES.</p>
